article.description: Matt Hauser had a career-high 29 points as Portland State defeated Cal State Northridge 73-67 on Friday night.
article.headline: Hauser carries Portland St. past CS Northridge 73-67
article.linkText: Hauser carries Portland St. past CS Northridge 73-67
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Matt Hauser had a career-high 29 points as Portland State defeated Cal State Northridge 73-67 on Friday night. Holland Woods had 14 points and 10 assists for Portland State (4-5). Lamar Hamrick added six rebounds. Rashaad Goolsby had 2 points and 16 rebounds for the hosts. After a tight first half that resulted in the two teams heading to the half tied at 36-36, Portland State outscored Cal State Northridge in the second half for the 6-point victory. The Matadors' 31 points in the second half were a season low for the team. Terrell Gomez had 21 points for the Matadors (2-8). Brendan Harrick added 18 points. Darius Brown II had 12 points and six assists. Portland State matches up against Portland Bible at home on Thursday. Cal State Northridge takes on North Dakota State at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
